  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The integration of Artificial Intelligence (AI) into educational settings has implied significant changes in teaching and learning methodologies.",
    "AI-driven tools, such as intelligent tutoring systems, educational chatbots, and personalized learning platforms, have shown considerable potential in reshaping the educational practices (Seo et al., 2021; Roll & Wylie, 2016).",
    "Research has demonstrated that these AIbased educational technologies can enhance student engagement by offering interactive and adaptive learning experiences, delivering instant and detailed feedback, and customizing instructional content to align with individual student needs and learning paces (Dai & Liu, 2024; Holmes & Tuomi, 2022).",
    "Consequently, these advancements may enforce educators to transform their teaching approaches to get more efficient and effective learning outcomes (Srinivasa et al., 2022; Zhai et al., 2021).",
    "Among all educational fields, programming education can be one of the complex domains as requiring mastery of logic, syntax, and problem-solving skills, which can vary greatly among students (Topalli & Cagiltay, 2018)."
  ],
